-- French Soldier Killed in Afghanistan, Hollande’s Office Says
-- B y   G r e g o r y   V i s c u s i
-- 2012-08-07T10:50:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-07/french-soldier-killed-in-afghanistan-hollande-s-office-says-1-.html
A French soldier was killed today in
a military operation in Afghanistan, President  Francois Hollande ’s office said in a statement.  Another soldier was injured during the joint operation with
the Afghan army in Kapisa province in the country’s northeast.
His life isn’t in danger, according to the statement.  A later statement from the Defense Ministry said the two
French Alpine soldiers were hit during a firefight while
accompanying an Afghan army patrol.  Today’s death brings to 88 the number of French military
personnel killed in Afghanistan since their arrival in 2001,
according to a count by  Agence France-Presse . France is due to
withdraw all its combat troops by the end of this year.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gregory Viscusi in Paris at 
 gviscusi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
